init_text: You're Barack Obama. 4 years into your retirement, you awake to find a letter with no return address on your bedside table. It reads "I hope you've had a chance to relax Barack...but pack your bags and call the number below. It's time to start the real job." Signed simply, "JFK."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You drive to a secluded beach on the Outer Banks of North Carolina and make your way to a small bungalow.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: JFK is sitting on the porch, wearing khaki's and a t-shirt, with his trademark rakish grin.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "So Barack, you ever get tired of retirement?

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: JFK explained that the success of the Democratic Party over the last two decades has piqued the interest of aliens.
